<p>A team of astrophysicist recently discovered a new black hole, the closest one to earth that was ever â€śobservedâ€ť. The article published in <em>Astronomy &amp; Astrophysics</em> comes from the European Southern Observatory in collaboration with other institutes. This new celestial object has been found in the Telescopium constellation with the help of the MPG/ESO 2.2-metre telescope located in the La Silla Observatory (Chile). It seems that the black hole is part of a three star system but so far its presence was only theorized since 2009.</p>

